# Pitfalls (do NOT do these)

## Yjs and FortuneSheet

- **Do NOT upgrade** `yjs`, `@y/protocols`, `@y/websocket-server`, or `y-websocket` without reading `docs/DECISIONS.md` § "Yjs / WebSocket npm compatibility." The versions are pinned to avoid a Yjs 13 vs 14 conflict that breaks WebSocket connections silently.
- **Do NOT attempt to reconstruct sheet state from the Yjs opLog on the server** for arbitrary live editing. The opLog contains serialized FortuneSheet ops that only FortuneSheet's `applyOp` can replay; the Yjs snapshot in the DB is the source of truth. **Exception:** controlled **server-side replay** in **`api/src/lib/yjs-oplog-replay.ts`** (export / preview / template flows) mutates sheet JSON directly — do **not** extend that path without understanding FortuneSheet op shapes and row/column index semantics.
- **Do NOT modify the FortuneSheet collaboration bridge** (the `onOp` → `yops.push` → `observe` → `applyOp` flow in **`web/src/lib/patchWorkbookCollab.ts`** / **`web/src/lib/patchWorkbookYjs.ts`**, wired from `PatchPage.tsx` / `PatchTemplateEditorPage.tsx`) unless you deeply understand both FortuneSheet ops and Yjs transactions.
- **Do NOT forget `ydoc.destroy()`** in cleanup effects when creating `Y.Doc` instances.
- **FortuneSheet** is consumed from a **source-level fork** (`doug86i/fortune-sheet`) as tarballs in **`vendor/`**. Do **NOT** use `patch-package` on FortuneSheet; all fixes go into the fork's TypeScript source. See **`.cursor/rules/patch-templates.mdc`** and **`docs/DECISIONS.md`**.

## Redis

- **Redis is NOT in the stack.** Do not import or configure Redis clients. If you need Redis, add the service to `docker-compose.yml` first and update `AGENTS.md`.

## Realtime sync

- Successful `POST` / `PATCH` / `DELETE` handlers that **should refresh** other users’ **domain / schedule / settings** UI **must** call **`broadcastInvalidate`** with **`queryKey` tuples** matching **`web/src/`**. Mutations with no REST-cached surface (e.g. internal housekeeping) are exempt — when unsure, see **`docs/REALTIME.md`** and **`.cursor/rules/realtime-and-data-sync.mdc`**.
- Every new **`useQuery`** key for that REST data must be covered by **`broadcastInvalidate`** in the relevant API mutations, or users need a manual refresh.
- Domain data uses **SSE**. Workbook data uses **Yjs/WebSocket**. Never mix them.

## Docker and testing

- **Classic (`make dev`):** changes are **not** live until you rebuild the **`app`** image — there is no bind-mount; the container serves **`web/dist`** + **`api/dist`**.
- **Fast (`make dev-fast`):** source is bind-mounted; **tsx** / **Vite** reload. Use this compose file for routine integration tests.
- **Do NOT** rely on **host-only** `npm run dev` against a non-Docker Postgres unless you know how to point **`DATABASE_URL`** at a running DB — the supported paths are **`make dev-fast`** and **`make dev`**.
- **Do NOT open saved HTML files** (`file://`) to test — they can't reach the API.

## Styling

- **Do NOT use hardcoded colors** (`#fff`, `rgba(...)`) — use CSS variables (`var(--color-on-brand)`, `var(--color-overlay)`).
- **Do NOT create new CSS files** — put styles in `web/src/global.css` or use existing classes.
- **Do NOT use raw `console.log`** in feature code — use **`req.log`** (API routes), **`createLogger`** (API off-request), or **`logDebug()`** (web); see **`.cursor/rules/logging.mdc`**.

## Schema and migrations

- **Do NOT edit existing migration files.** Create a new `api/drizzle/NNNN_<name>.sql` and update `meta/_journal.json`.
- **Do NOT manually run SQL** against the database. All schema changes go through Drizzle migrations.

## Dependencies

- **Do NOT add dependencies** without checking they are MIT/compatible (see `docs/LICENSING.md`).
- **Do NOT modify `package-lock.json` manually** — only `npm install` should touch it.
